Hey, it's me, Jeffrey.

935
01:02:13,773 --> 01:02:18,970
Mild-mannered toy-store clerk by day,
purveyor of childhood fantasies by night.

936
01:02:19,070 --> 01:02:20,513
For a price.

937
01:02:20,613 --> 01:02:26,552
And since we all have our cards on the table,
I brought a little backup of my own.

938
01:02:28,788 --> 01:02:29,897
Little backup?

939
01:02:29,997 --> 01:02:33,860
- Oh, he meant that literally, didn't he?
- I knew elves were for real.

940
01:02:33,960 --> 01:02:37,071
That's not an elf, brother.
That's the dude from <i>Taxi.</i>

941
01:02:37,171 --> 01:02:41,743
Sebastian is a temporary
coworker at Toy Traders.

942
01:02:41,843 --> 01:02:44,746
What are y'all doing down
here scalping Harrison Bears?

943
01:02:44,846 --> 01:02:46,539
It's weird. Doesn't make any sense.

944
01:02:46,639 --> 01:02:50,585
Because I have big plans, Larry. Big plans.
And I'll tell you something for free.

945
01:02:50,685 --> 01:02:52,670
They don't involve waiting five years...

946
01:02:52,770 --> 01:02:55,965
to become a junior assistant
associate manager at Toy Traders...

947
01:02:56,065 --> 01:02:59,761
nor do they involve dealing with
obnoxious parents like you...

948
01:02:59,861 --> 01:03:04,966
who yell at me when I can't magically
produce whatever toy their kids want.

949
01:03:06,034 --> 01:03:07,635
Let's cut to the brass tacks.

950
01:03:09,037 --> 01:03:12,974
- You got the money?
- Yeah, I got the money.

951
01:03:14,167 --> 01:03:17,779
- Do you got the item?
- Yeah, we got the item.

952
01:03:17,879 --> 01:03:19,605
All right.

953
01:03:21,049 --> 01:03:23,952
<i>Hi, I'm Harrison. What's your name?</i>

954
01:03:24,052 --> 01:03:25,662
Oh, shut up.

955
01:03:25,762 --> 01:03:29,290
<i>Hi, Shut Up. Nice to meet you.</i>

956
01:03:29,390 --> 01:03:32,502
I really hate these things.

957
01:03:32,602 --> 01:03:34,162
Okay, let's see the cash.

958
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:37,832
- There it is.
- My associate will count it.

959
01:03:39,108 --> 01:03:42,837
- It's all there.
- We're gonna find out if it's all there.

960
01:03:43,488 --> 01:03:45,590
How's it look? Great.

961
01:03:48,534 --> 01:03:50,428
Looks like your quest is over, Larry.

962
01:03:50,745 --> 01:03:54,015
Oh, man. This is finally gonna be over.

963
01:03:54,707 --> 01:03:56,684
Police. Everybody freeze.

964
01:03:58,920 --> 01:04:01,689
- I knew they were monitoring my phone.
- Put your hands up.

965
01:04:03,049 --> 01:04:04,826
Don't shoot. My father is a veteran.

966
01:04:04,926 --> 01:04:09,030
- Sebastian, hide the evidence.
- You ain't going anywhere with that bear.

967
01:04:13,101 --> 01:04:14,786
Freeze.

968
01:04:15,269 --> 01:04:17,371
Hi.

969
01:04:17,939 --> 01:04:21,209
There's gotta be a better way to
get your Christmas shopping done.

970
01:04:24,028 --> 01:04:25,221
I didn't steal those.

971
01:04:25,321 --> 01:04:29,142
Just because I work at a toy store doesn't
mean those bears came from that store.

972
01:04:29,242 --> 01:04:31,603
I'm sure the judge will
wanna hear all about that.

973
01:04:31,703 --> 01:04:34,856
Thank you. We'll be in touch in
case we need you two as witnesses.

974
01:04:34,956 --> 01:04:38,860
- What are you gonna do with all them bears?
- They're being impounded as evidence.

975
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:41,946
You think maybe I could get one
for my daughter for Christmas?

976
01:04:42,046 --> 01:04:45,658
- I'm sorry, sir, we can't do that.
- But you have so many. We just need one.

977
01:04:45,758 --> 01:04:47,035
Yeah, I'll even buy one.

978
01:04:47,135 --> 01:04:49,662
I'm sorry, sir. They all
have to be accounted for.

979
01:04:49,762 --> 01:04:52,540
You two have a good night.
Happy holidays.

980
01:04:52,640 --> 01:04:56,878
Yeah, and a merry Christmas to you too
and all that... All that other stuff.

981
01:04:56,978 --> 01:05:00,381
Well, at least we got the money back.

982
01:05:00,481 --> 01:05:02,959
- Well, that's good.
- Yeah.

983
01:05:05,737 --> 01:05:08,389
If I tell you something,
you promise not to laugh at me?

984
01:05:08,489 --> 01:05:09,724
Sure.

985
01:05:09,824 --> 01:05:14,220
When that elf flipped me,
I pooped my pants a little.

986
01:05:21,544 --> 01:05:25,406
You guys going to the tree
lighting tonight? Looks fun.

987
01:05:25,506 --> 01:05:28,109
I'm going. You going, Lar?

988
01:05:29,761 --> 01:05:32,664
You know what, Claude?
I'm beginning to think you were right.

989
01:05:32,764 --> 01:05:33,915
- Really?
- Yup.

990
01:05:34,015 --> 01:05:35,416
About what?

991
01:05:35,516 --> 01:05:38,086
It's ridiculous to think I
could compete with Victor.

992
01:05:38,186 --> 01:05:41,673
- Oh, it's about time.
- It is about time.

993
01:05:41,773 --> 01:05:44,634
It's about time I realized that
Christmas is about giving...

994
01:05:44,734 --> 01:05:46,844
not who's taking credit for something.

995
01:05:46,944 --> 01:05:50,765
And it's about spending time with my
daughter, not fighting with her stepdad.

996
01:05:50,865 --> 01:05:53,050
That's the spirit.

997
01:05:53,242 --> 01:05:55,489
I'm really glad to hear
you say that, Larry.

998
01:05:55,589 --> 01:05:57,647
Yeah. Yeah. Tell you what.

999
01:05:57,747 --> 01:06:00,640
What a better time than a tree
lighting to show a little

1000
01:06:00,740 --> 01:06:02,944
peace and goodwill toward Victor?

1001
01:06:03,044 --> 01:06:07,448
I mean, you know, there's plenty of
room for both of us in Noel's life.

1002
01:06:07,548 --> 01:06:09,200
- Besides...
- Hey, check this out.

1003
01:06:09,300 --> 01:06:12,078
<i>Parents everywhere have been
frustrated this Christmas...</i>

1004
01:06:12,178 --> 01:06:16,708
<i>by the fact that there are no more
Harrison Talking Bears on toy shelves.</i>

1005
01:06:16,808 --> 01:06:18,566
<i>How do you look your kid
in the eye and tell him</i>

1006
01:06:18,666 --> 01:06:21,421
<i>Santa can't give him the
one thing he wants?</i>

1007
01:06:21,562 --> 01:06:25,466
<i>She looks up at me and says, "But,
Mommy, it's the only thing I want."</i>

1008
01:06:25,566 --> 01:06:27,385
<i>It just breaks my heart.</i>

1009
01:06:27,485 --> 01:06:30,638
<i>But there is a new wrinkle that
has developed in this story.</i>

1010
01:06:30,738 --> 01:06:34,309
<i>According to various reports and
in the words of one manager...</i>

1011
01:06:34,409 --> 01:06:39,939
<i>there were plenty of Harrison Talking Bears
in stock as recently as a few days ago.</i>

1012
01:06:40,039 --> 01:06:43,651
<i>But according to various
witnesses in toy stores...</i>

1013
01:06:43,751 --> 01:06:46,321
<i>all the remaining Harrison
Bears were bought up...</i>

1014
01:06:46,421 --> 01:06:50,491
<i>by the same unidentified
white male in large lots...</i>

1015
01:06:50,591 --> 01:06:54,078
<i>perhaps to be sold on the black
market to desperate parents.</i>

1016
01:06:54,178 --> 01:06:59,000
<i>And so it would seem someone somewhere
is hoarding Harrison Talking Bears.</i>

1017
01:06:59,100 --> 01:07:01,336
<i>- For Channel One News....</i>
- That is crazy.

1018
01:07:01,436 --> 01:07:05,465
Yeah. I mean, somebody would have
to have a whole lot of money...

1019
01:07:05,565 --> 01:07:07,834
to buy every single bear in town.

1020
01:07:09,485 --> 01:07:13,181
And who do we know that
has a whole lot of money?

1021
01:07:13,281 --> 01:07:16,142
You don't think Victor had
something to do with this, do you?

1022
01:07:16,242 --> 01:07:18,895
Yeah, Claude, I do.

1023
01:07:18,995 --> 01:07:20,939
Claude, he knows. He knows.

1024
01:07:21,039 --> 01:07:23,474
He must have found out
what was in Noel's letter.

1025
01:07:24,459 --> 01:07:28,321
Man, I'm out of here. I'll see you
down at the tree lighting later.

1026
01:07:28,421 --> 01:07:29,697
Where are you going?

1027
01:07:29,797 --> 01:07:32,992
If Victor's been buying these bears,
I know where he's keeping them.

1028
01:07:33,092 --> 01:07:35,903
I'm gonna go there, I'm gonna
get me one of them bears.

1029
01:07:36,262 --> 01:07:40,199
When I get one, down goes Victor.

1030
01:07:52,320 --> 01:07:54,922
- Good night, Betsy.
- See you at the ceremony.

1031
01:07:59,702 --> 01:08:01,354
Hey, you closing early?

1032
01:08:01,454 --> 01:08:04,565
Our company is sponsoring the
tree-lighting event this evening.

1033
01:08:04,665 --> 01:08:06,526
A lot of us are heading over there.

1034
01:08:06,626 --> 01:08:10,029
Hey, that's good. Well, I got a
package here for Victor Baxter.

1035
01:08:10,129 --> 01:08:13,366
- Oh, thanks. I can sign for it.
- You ain't gonna believe this.

1036
01:08:13,466 --> 01:08:17,412
A couple of women on their way in thought
I looked like Brad Pitt. You believe that?

1037
01:08:17,512 --> 01:08:18,863
Yeah, a little. Yeah.

1038
01:08:19,681 --> 01:08:23,084
All right. Hey, do me a favor.
Make sure this gets up to him fast, okay?

1039
01:08:23,184 --> 01:08:26,462
- It says "urgent" right on there.
- I'll take it up to him right away.

1040
01:08:26,562 --> 01:08:30,208
Good. And tell him it has something to
do with Operation Who's Your Daddy.

1041
01:08:31,651 --> 01:08:33,127
And I hate doing it to you.

1042
01:08:33,820 --> 01:08:35,797
You got a toilet in here?

1043
01:08:36,948 --> 01:08:41,219
- Yeah.
- Yes. It's just down the hall on the right.

1044
01:08:42,286 --> 01:08:45,648
You're a lifesaver.
Merry Christmas to you.

1045
01:08:45,748 --> 01:08:48,559
- Brad Pitt.
- Brad Pitt.

1046
01:08:50,586 --> 01:08:52,488
Yeah. Yeah.

1047
01:08:52,588 --> 01:08:55,283
- Mr. Baxter.
- Yeah, I'm leaving now.

1048
01:08:55,383 --> 01:08:58,453
Yeah. I'll see you downtown right
next to the tree. Love you too.

1049
01:08:58,553 --> 01:09:01,989
Perfect timing. I was just
bringing this package up to you.

1050
01:09:02,348 --> 01:09:04,751
- It just arrived. They said it was urgent.
- Thanks.

1051
01:09:04,851 --> 01:09:10,623
And the delivery guy said it was for
something called Operation Who's Your Daddy.

1052
01:09:11,441 --> 01:09:14,719
Really? It must be from Welling.

1053
01:09:14,819 --> 01:09:18,139
I'll see you at the tree lighting.
I'm looking forward to your speech.

1054
01:09:18,239 --> 01:09:19,632
Me too.

1055
01:09:29,917 --> 01:09:31,986
That's right, Victor.

1056
01:09:32,086 --> 01:09:35,440
Take me right to Harrison.

1057
01:09:41,637 --> 01:09:43,698
Where is Victor Baxter?

1058
01:09:46,726 --> 01:09:48,202
Oh, no, no, no.

1059
01:09:53,024 --> 01:09:56,169
- It's empty.
- That's the point.

1060
01:09:58,988 --> 01:10:01,975
Go, go, go.

1061
01:10:02,075 --> 01:10:05,687
- No, no, do not touch that.
- Hey, this is so beautiful.

1062
01:10:05,787 --> 01:10:08,147
- Where's Larry?
- Last-minute Christmas shopping.

1063
01:10:08,247 --> 01:10:10,650
- Did he find that bear?
- We'll see.

1064
01:10:10,750 --> 01:10:13,528
Oh, hey, Sharon, Mike. Hi.

1065
01:10:13,628 --> 01:10:16,281
- Now, this is what I call....
- The Christmas spirit.

1066
01:10:16,381 --> 01:10:18,491
- Indeed.
- Indeed.

1067
01:10:18,591 --> 01:10:20,702
This is so beautiful.

1068
01:10:20,802 --> 01:10:25,698
- And our family's putting on the event.
- That's right, sweet pea.

1069
01:11:23,698 --> 01:11:27,301
- Is this supposed to be a joke?
- Yeah, and you're the punch line.

1070
01:11:30,538 --> 01:11:32,231
Biscuits and gravy.

1071
01:11:32,331 --> 01:11:34,609
Larry, this is not what it looks like.

1072
01:11:34,709 --> 01:11:38,312
It looks like you've been buying these
Harrison Bears so I can't get one.

1073
01:11:38,588 --> 01:11:40,531
Okay, maybe it is what it looks like.

1074
01:11:40,631 --> 01:11:44,577
Well, that's the lowest of the low, Victor.
You know that? You're an idiot.

1075
01:11:44,677 --> 01:11:48,915
To get back at me, you're gonna make sure
Noel don't get the Christmas she most wants.

1076
01:11:49,015 --> 01:11:52,627
No, no, no. She's gonna get a
Harrison Talking Bear, all right.

1077
01:11:52,727 --> 01:11:55,880
Only it's coming from her new
dad instead of her old one.

1078
01:11:55,980 --> 01:12:00,134
- It will be the first present she opens.
- When she opens it up, know what she'll say?

1079
01:12:00,234 --> 01:12:02,303
"Thanks, but I already
got a Harrison Bear.

1080
01:12:02,403 --> 01:12:05,473
- Dad gave it to me at the tree lighting."
- You wouldn't dare.

1081
01:12:05,573 --> 01:12:08,977
The last couple of days, you'd be
surprised what I'd do for my daughter.

1082
01:12:09,077 --> 01:12:10,937
- Is that a leak?
- No, we don't have...

1083
01:12:11,037 --> 01:12:13,806
- Hey, not so fast.
- See you later.

1084
01:12:14,415 --> 01:12:16,359
Get off me.

1085
01:12:16,459 --> 01:12:18,686
Get off me.

1086
01:12:20,129 --> 01:12:23,199
Great. Now look what you've done.

1087
01:12:23,299 --> 01:12:25,994
I didn't do nothing. I ain't
gonna pay for a new handle.

1088
01:12:26,094 --> 01:12:28,621
No, you idiot. We're locked in.

1089
01:12:28,721 --> 01:12:31,583
- What do you mean we're locked in?
- I mean we're locked in.

1090
01:12:31,683 --> 01:12:32,825
Are you kidding me?

1091
01:12:34,227 --> 01:12:38,631
Hey! Ain't you got another door,
like another way out or something?

1092
01:12:38,731 --> 01:12:41,876
Afraid not. And no one's
coming back for two days.

1093
01:12:42,610 --> 01:12:46,848
You mean we're trapped in here for two days?
I'm gonna miss Christmas with my little girl?

1094
01:12:46,948 --> 01:12:49,517
And I'm gonna have to
spend it with you? Help!

1095
01:12:49,617 --> 01:12:53,387
Hello! Hey! Open sesame.

1096
01:12:54,539 --> 01:12:55,973
Help!

1097
01:12:57,083 --> 01:12:59,811
You're wasting your time.
It's locked from the outside.

1098
01:13:01,796 --> 01:13:04,398
Nice job, genius.

1099
01:13:04,716 --> 01:13:06,025
What?

1100
01:13:09,053 --> 01:13:10,446
<i>Hi, I'm Harrison.</i>

1101
01:13:11,973 --> 01:13:13,333
<i>Leave a message.</i>

1102
01:13:13,433 --> 01:13:15,835
Hi, Victor.
Just wondering where you are.

1103
01:13:15,935 --> 01:13:18,671
We're here at the
tree-lighting ceremony.

1104
01:13:18,771 --> 01:13:22,083
I guess we'll just see you
when you get here. Okay. Bye.

1105
01:13:22,483 --> 01:13:24,886
Is Victor coming soon?

1106
01:13:24,986 --> 01:13:28,348
He's probably on his
way right now. Come on.

1107
01:13:28,448 --> 01:13:29,849
Excuse me.

1108
01:13:29,949 --> 01:13:34,095
Hi, are you Nate Welling, head of
security for Baxter Box Company?

1109
01:13:34,871 --> 01:13:37,148
- Yes.
- Would you like to comment...

1110
01:13:37,248 --> 01:13:40,151
on the sudden shortage
of Harrison Talking Bears...

1111
01:13:40,251 --> 01:13:41,819
in toy stores all over town?

1112
01:13:41,919 --> 01:13:43,863
I was not aware of that.

1113
01:13:43,963 --> 01:13:47,158
You were not aware that a man
has been going around...

1114
01:13:47,258 --> 01:13:50,495
and buying up all the Harrison
Talking Bears in bulk...

1115
01:13:50,595 --> 01:13:53,114
thereby creating a shortage
just before Christmas?

1116
01:13:53,681 --> 01:13:56,084
Well, I know about it now.

1117
01:13:56,184 --> 01:13:59,003
It seems that every bear has
been bought and paid for...

1118
01:13:59,103 --> 01:14:02,048
by a Baxter Box Company credit card.

1119
01:14:02,148 --> 01:14:04,926
And all the bears have been
signed and paid for...

1120
01:14:05,026 --> 01:14:07,587
by someone named N. Welling.

1121
01:14:08,321 --> 01:14:11,432
- That would be you, wouldn't it?
- Not necessarily.

1122
01:14:11,532 --> 01:14:15,728
Oh, so there is more than one N.
Welling working at Baxter Box Company?

1123
01:14:15,828 --> 01:14:19,857
Why would I buy up Harrison
Talking Bears? I don't even have kids.

1124
01:14:19,957 --> 01:14:24,195
How about Victor Baxter,
the president of Baxter Box Company?

1125
01:14:24,295 --> 01:14:27,648
- Would he have something to do with this?
- No, absolutely not.

1126
01:14:28,174 --> 01:14:31,911
Oh, so this is something that
you are doing on your own.

1127
01:14:32,011 --> 01:14:34,322
You greedy jerk.

1128
01:14:34,889 --> 01:14:38,042
My little girl wanted one of those
bears more than anything else.

1129
01:14:38,142 --> 01:14:39,660
You ruined her Christmas.

1130
01:14:40,937 --> 01:14:42,880
No comment.

1131
01:14:42,980 --> 01:14:44,215
- I mean...
- How dare you?

1132
01:14:44,315 --> 01:14:47,168
- Shame on you.
- I wasn't trying to ruin anyone's Christmas.

1133
01:14:47,777 --> 01:14:52,223
Well, then what were you trying
to do, then, Mr. Welling?

1134
01:14:52,323 --> 01:14:55,393
- What's the deal here?
- Yeah, what's going on?

1135
01:14:55,493 --> 01:14:57,979
- What is the meaning of this?
- We want the truth.

1136
01:14:58,079 --> 01:14:59,522
We want the truth.

1137
01:14:59,622 --> 01:15:03,192
<i>We want the truth. We want the truth.</i>

1138
01:15:03,292 --> 01:15:06,145
It wasn't me. It was Victor Baxter.

1139
01:15:07,672 --> 01:15:11,409
He made me buy up all the bears. I was
just doing what my employer told me to.

1140
01:15:11,509 --> 01:15:14,695
- How dare you?
- So Victor Baxter is responsible for this.

1141
01:15:18,307 --> 01:15:20,919
- Yes.
- You big meanie.

1142
01:15:21,019 --> 01:15:22,537
- Shame on you.
- Hey.

1143
01:15:30,236 --> 01:15:32,680
<i>- Hey.</i>
- I'm about to teach you a little humility.

1144
01:15:32,780 --> 01:15:35,216
<i>Harrison loves exercise.</i>

1145
01:15:36,117 --> 01:15:37,602
<i>- Let's play.</i>
- Yeah, well...

1146
01:15:37,702 --> 01:15:39,520
<i>- Hey, that's...</i>
- Humility this.

1147
01:15:39,620 --> 01:15:44,142
<i>Will you be my friend? I love you.</i>

1148
01:15:46,502 --> 01:15:49,197
- What the heck was that?
- I'm warning you.

1149
01:15:49,297 --> 01:15:52,283
I've watched <i>The Matrix </i>37 times.

1150
01:15:52,383 --> 01:15:55,403
<i>- Let's play.</i>
- You need to get out of the house more.

1151
01:15:56,304 --> 01:15:58,239
Let's bear-knuckle it, boys.

1152
01:15:58,639 --> 01:15:59,740
That's it.

1153
01:16:02,268 --> 01:16:03,828
Come on, son.

1154
01:16:06,314 --> 01:16:07,582
Come on.

1155
01:16:09,067 --> 01:16:13,004
- Hit him with the southpaw.
- That's a good one. Right there.

1156
01:16:15,490 --> 01:16:17,925
- Time-out. Time-out. Time-out.<i>
- That tickles.</i>

1157
01:16:19,660 --> 01:16:22,397
You know you started this
whole thing, you know.

1158
01:16:22,497 --> 01:16:25,567
Talking about what we're gonna do
for Christmas in front of Noel.

1159
01:16:25,667 --> 01:16:28,236
I admit that was a mistake.

1160
01:16:28,336 --> 01:16:31,939
It's my first Christmas with Noel,
and I wanted it to go well.

1161
01:16:32,674 --> 01:16:36,869
- Besides, I've never been a dad before.
- You're a stepdad.

1162
01:16:36,969 --> 01:16:39,664
And there it is right there.

1163
01:16:39,764 --> 01:16:42,166
- What? Where? What?
- "What? Where? What?"

1164
01:16:42,266 --> 01:16:46,746
The way you just said "stepdad."
Like it was some kind of lower form of life.

1165
01:16:49,440 --> 01:16:53,428
You know, it is not easy competing
with Mr. Perfect-Dad, you know.

1166
01:16:53,528 --> 01:16:56,389
Perfect-Dad? Are you kidding me?

1167
01:16:56,489 --> 01:16:59,767
By avoiding any semblance
of responsibility...

1168
01:16:59,867 --> 01:17:02,145
you're always happy and relaxed.

1169
01:17:02,245 --> 01:17:04,939
And since you work
as little as possible...

1170
01:17:05,039 --> 01:17:08,943
you're always free to take her
places and do things with her.

1171
01:17:09,043 --> 01:17:13,773
So that's it. So since you think I'm
a failure, I'm a winner in Noel's eyes.

1172
01:17:15,299 --> 01:17:16,659
Let me tell you something...

1173
01:17:16,759 --> 01:17:20,371
Mr. I-Paid-$40,000-to-Get-All-These
Harrison-Bears-so-I-Couldn't-Get-One.

1174
01:17:20,471 --> 01:17:23,291
I pay all my taxes.
I don't owe a cent to anybody.

1175
01:17:23,391 --> 01:17:26,628
I ain't never took a handout,
and I take care of my support for Noel.

1176
01:17:26,728 --> 01:17:30,498
And I ain't gotta apologize to
anybody for nothing, especially you.

1177
01:17:31,733 --> 01:17:33,259
Okay, fair enough.

1178
01:17:33,359 --> 01:17:35,970
Well, try explaining that to
a little 8-year-old girl...

1179
01:17:36,070 --> 01:17:38,932
whose stepdad lives in a
mansion and has a chef...

1180
01:17:39,032 --> 01:17:42,268
and can buy her anything he
wants anytime she wants it.

1181
01:17:42,368 --> 01:17:46,439
Okay, I see. So the problem
is I'm too successful.

1182
01:17:46,539 --> 01:17:48,840
Well, let me tell you something, bub.

1183
01:17:48,940 --> 01:17:52,528
Like you, I have never taken anything
from anybody. I work hard for what I have.

1184
01:17:52,628 --> 01:17:56,157
Victor, I'm not begrudging your success,
okay? I'm very happy for you.

1185
01:17:56,257 --> 01:17:59,452
It ain't about that, all right?

1186
01:17:59,552 --> 01:18:01,996
It's about Noel.

1187
01:18:02,096 --> 01:18:06,492
It's about me trying to
compete with you. I can't do it.

1188
01:18:07,769 --> 01:18:10,463
I'm not sure I'm ever gonna
learn to like you, okay?

1189
01:18:10,563 --> 01:18:13,508
- Or me you.
- But because of Noel...

1190
01:18:13,608 --> 01:18:16,010
I'm stuck with you,
and you're stuck with me.

1191
01:18:16,110 --> 01:18:19,338
So we gotta figure out a
way to get along, okay?

1192
01:18:19,906 --> 01:18:24,310
Okay. Agreed. That doesn't change
the fact that we're still stuck in here.

1193
01:18:24,410 --> 01:18:26,229
We need to find some way to get out...

1194
01:18:26,329 --> 01:18:29,607
or Noel ain't gonna have any one
of her dads there for Christmas.

1195
01:18:29,707 --> 01:18:31,734
Cell phones.

1196
01:18:31,834 --> 01:18:34,395
Come on. Here we go.

1197
01:18:37,298 --> 01:18:40,151
- I got no reception.
- Me either. Metal building.

1198
01:18:43,388 --> 01:18:46,124
- That's a good one. I haven't seen that one.
- You like it?

1199
01:18:46,224 --> 01:18:48,042
- Look at that.
- Look at that.

1200
01:18:48,142 --> 01:18:50,962
Look at that umbrella she got.

1201
01:18:51,062 --> 01:18:54,081
I'll tell you what,
that's from us at the fair.

1202
01:18:55,817 --> 01:18:59,554
- Well, we gotta get out of here.
- Yes, we do.

1203
01:18:59,654 --> 01:19:02,390
If I got out of high school,
I can get out of this place.

1204
01:19:02,490 --> 01:19:04,851
This time it ain't gonna take six years.

1205
01:19:04,951 --> 01:19:07,929
I'm just kidding, Vic. Five.

1206
01:19:14,627 --> 01:19:16,946
Yeah. Christmas is back on, baby.

1207
01:19:17,046 --> 01:19:19,407
- Well done, Larry.
- Okay, here's the plan.

1208
01:19:19,507 --> 01:19:22,744
What I'll do then is I'll just head
by the Christmas-tree lighting...

1209
01:19:22,844 --> 01:19:25,288
and I'll pick up Noel for
Christmas number one.

1210
01:19:25,388 --> 01:19:29,125
Then Trish and I will come by tomorrow
to pick her up for Christmas number two.

1211
01:19:29,225 --> 01:19:30,835
Yeah, I guess that'll work.

1212
01:19:30,935 --> 01:19:33,212
- Why don't we do Christmas together?
- Together.

1213
01:19:33,312 --> 01:19:36,090
- I was just gonna say that.
- I was thinking the same thing.

1214
01:19:36,190 --> 01:19:39,677
Come by my house. I'm an unbelievable cook.
I got... I make good turkey.

1215
01:19:39,777 --> 01:19:41,596
- Awesome.
- All right.

1216
01:19:41,696 --> 01:19:42,839
Let's call Trish.

1217
01:19:43,031 --> 01:19:47,268
<i>Down with Baxter Boxes!
Down with Baxter Boxes!</i>

1218
01:19:47,368 --> 01:19:48,937
<i>Down with Baxter Boxes!</i>

1219
01:19:49,037 --> 01:19:50,730
Victor, where have you been?

1220
01:19:50,830 --> 01:19:52,857
It's a long story.

1221
01:19:52,957 --> 01:19:56,236
Well, Larry's missing too.
He never came to pick up Noel.

1222
01:19:56,336 --> 01:19:59,405
Oh, hi, Trish. I'm here too,
which is another long story.

1223
01:19:59,505 --> 01:20:01,399
Yeah, we were just coming to meet you.

1224
01:20:01,924 --> 01:20:05,787
Well, you better not come down, Victor.
It's gotten completely out of control.

1225
01:20:05,887 --> 01:20:07,622
What are you talking about?

1226
01:20:07,722 --> 01:20:11,459
Somehow everyone's gotten the idea that
you bought up all the Harrison Bears...

1227
01:20:11,559 --> 01:20:13,670
so that no one else could have one.

1228
01:20:13,770 --> 01:20:15,079
Is that true?

1229
01:20:16,064 --> 01:20:19,133
In a manner of speaking,
it's another long story.

1230
01:20:19,233 --> 01:20:20,635
I'll explain it all later.

1231
01:20:20,735 --> 01:20:26,140
Well, they're calling you Ebenezer
Baxter and Victor the Grinch.

1232
01:20:26,240 --> 01:20:29,686
You just shouldn't even show
your face down here, Victor.

1233
01:20:29,786 --> 01:20:31,479
It's not safe.

1234
01:20:31,579 --> 01:20:35,141
All right. Thanks for
the heads-up. Bye, hon.

1235
01:20:39,712 --> 01:20:43,658
- Come on, honey.
- Why is everybody so mad at Victor?

1236
01:20:43,758 --> 01:20:47,662
It's.... It's complicated.

1237
01:20:47,762 --> 01:20:51,291
The Baxter name has been one of the
most respected in town for 70 years...

1238
01:20:51,391 --> 01:20:53,668
and in one night, I destroy it.

1239
01:20:53,768 --> 01:20:55,587
Hold on, Victor.

1240
01:20:55,687 --> 01:20:59,340
Even though you deserve everything
you got coming to you...

1241
01:20:59,440 --> 01:21:01,259
I feel sorry for you, okay?

1242
01:21:01,359 --> 01:21:05,179
- Thank you. But, Larry, everyone hates me.
- Everybody doesn't hate you.

1243
01:21:05,279 --> 01:21:06,389
Trish likes you.

1244
01:21:06,489 --> 01:21:08,891
Well, she's married to me.
She has to like me.

1245
01:21:08,991 --> 01:21:10,968
Well, Noel likes you.

1246
01:21:11,953 --> 01:21:13,554
- Really?
- Yeah.

1247
01:21:14,455 --> 01:21:16,390
Gotta say, I think she loves you.

1248
01:21:19,085 --> 01:21:22,814
And I'll be honest. I'm kind of starting
to not dislike like you myself.

1249
01:21:26,009 --> 01:21:29,987
I guess I should head home and
barricade the doors for the angry mob.

1250
01:21:31,014 --> 01:21:33,407
Hey, wait a second.

1251
01:21:33,641 --> 01:21:35,910
We're going to that
Christmas-tree lighting.

1252
01:21:36,602 --> 01:21:38,630
Are you crazy?
Did you hear what she said?

1253
01:21:38,730 --> 01:21:41,758
- They'll kill me. I can't go back there.
- I got an idea.

1254
01:21:41,858 --> 01:21:45,887
If it works, you're gonna go from town
goat to town hero in about 10 minutes.

1255
01:21:45,987 --> 01:21:47,588
And if you're wrong?

1256
01:21:48,156 --> 01:21:49,882
I'll be one of your pallbearers.

1257
01:21:52,994 --> 01:21:55,146
Dead man walking.

1258
01:21:55,246 --> 01:21:59,609
<i>Down with Baxter Boxes!
Down with Baxter Boxes!</i>

1259
01:21:59,709 --> 01:22:04,739
<i>Down with Baxter Boxes!
Down with Baxter Boxes!</i>

1260
01:22:04,839 --> 01:22:08,067
Hey. Hey, there's the Baxter Box truck.

1261
01:22:21,481 --> 01:22:23,841
- Victor, are you ready?
- I don't know about this.

1262
01:22:23,941 --> 01:22:28,096
- It's gonna take a miracle for this to work.
- It's Christmas. It's a time for miracles.

1263
01:22:28,196 --> 01:22:31,382
- Just have a little faith, buddy.
- Well, you know, I just...

1264
01:22:35,453 --> 01:22:38,523
Can I have your attention, please?
Can I have your attention...?

1265
01:22:38,623 --> 01:22:41,276
Can I have your attention, please?

1266
01:22:41,376 --> 01:22:43,361
What's Daddy doing?

1267
01:22:43,461 --> 01:22:46,105
I don't know what
he's doing, sweetheart.

1268
01:22:48,341 --> 01:22:51,536
Come on, stop. Would you knock it off?
I'm trying to say something.

1269
01:22:51,636 --> 01:22:53,321
I'm trying to speak!

1270
01:23:00,687 --> 01:23:03,631
Everybody, please, just zip it.

1271
01:23:03,731 --> 01:23:05,666
Let the man speak!

1272
01:23:06,025 --> 01:23:07,719
- Please.
- Thank you.

1273
01:23:07,819 --> 01:23:12,140
Apparently, a lot of y'all here have been
given some inaccurate information...

1274
01:23:12,240 --> 01:23:15,968
about Victor Baxter and Baxter Boxes.

1275
01:23:17,078 --> 01:23:18,930
Hold on! Let me speak!

1276
01:23:19,330 --> 01:23:22,567
I'm here to tell you you got it
all wrong about Victor Baxter.

1277
01:23:22,667 --> 01:23:26,779
He's not here to ruin Christmas.
He's here to make it better.

1278
01:23:26,879 --> 01:23:29,365
No! Listen! Just hold on!

1279
01:23:29,465 --> 01:23:35,246
Cool it! This whole thing was a
surprise by the Baxter Box Company...

1280
01:23:35,346 --> 01:23:38,833
and it has been planned for a
long time, and it fooled even me.

1281
01:23:38,933 --> 01:23:41,294
Let me show you what I mean.
Everybody, follow me.

1282
01:23:41,394 --> 01:23:42,670
Please. Follow me, please.

1283
01:23:42,770 --> 01:23:45,423
- Stand back. Follow me.
- Seriously, no more lying...

1284
01:23:45,523 --> 01:23:47,467
Hold on. Ladies and gentlemen...

1285
01:23:47,567 --> 01:23:51,137
compliments of Victor Baxter
and the Baxter Box Company...

1286
01:23:51,237 --> 01:23:53,714
merry Christmas.

1287
01:23:57,285 --> 01:23:59,220
Look at it, Mommy.

1288
01:23:59,537 --> 01:24:02,140
- So many bears.
- The bears!

1289
01:24:03,583 --> 01:24:05,059
Victor, say your line.

1290
01:24:05,501 --> 01:24:07,895
- What line?
- Your line.

1291
01:24:11,966 --> 01:24:14,902
Merry Christmas from Baxter Box Company.

1292
01:24:15,762 --> 01:24:19,991
I have free Harrison Bears
for everybody who wants one.

1293
01:24:26,647 --> 01:24:28,166
It's a miracle.

1294
01:24:32,987 --> 01:24:34,338
Yeah?

1295
01:24:35,448 --> 01:24:37,758
Merry Christmas.

1296
01:24:38,201 --> 01:24:39,727
There you are. Merry Christmas.

1297
01:24:39,827 --> 01:24:40,937
- Hey, Lar.
- Yeah?

1298
01:24:41,037 --> 01:24:43,064
- I owe you one.
- Darn right you do.

1299
01:24:43,164 --> 01:24:46,267
Don't think I'm gonna let
you forget about it later.

1300
01:24:47,251 --> 01:24:51,105
- Thank you. Thank you so much.<i>
- Happy Holidays.</i>

1301
01:24:51,756 --> 01:24:54,108
- Thank you, Santa.
- Merry Christmas.

1302
01:24:55,677 --> 01:25:00,281
Merry Christmas to everybody
from Baxter Boxes.

1303
01:25:24,122 --> 01:25:26,649
- Can I open my present now, please?
- Yeah.

1304
01:25:26,749 --> 01:25:29,110
- This one is from me.
- And me.

1305
01:25:29,210 --> 01:25:30,603
Okay, it's from both of you.

1306
01:25:31,004 --> 01:25:34,440
- Right, guys?
- That's right. It was my idea, though.

1307
01:25:41,723 --> 01:25:43,449
What is it?

1308
01:25:43,850 --> 01:25:45,618
Hey!

1309
01:25:49,272 --> 01:25:51,833
- Honey?
- Thanks.

1310
01:25:52,900 --> 01:25:56,054
- Honey, that's a Harrison.
- The Talking Bear.

1311
01:25:56,154 --> 01:25:59,057
Yeah, I know. Like, you handed
them out at the tree lighting.

1312
01:25:59,157 --> 01:26:02,143
But wasn't Harrison what you asked
for in your letter to Santa?

1313
01:26:02,243 --> 01:26:06,564
Dad, you said you wouldn't show
anyone my letter except Santa.

1314
01:26:06,664 --> 01:26:07,857
Yeah....

1315
01:26:07,957 --> 01:26:11,694
Santa Claus dropped it the other night,
and Victor come along and picked it up.

1316
01:26:11,794 --> 01:26:16,324
I did. I did. I found it.
And then I gave it back to Larry.

1317
01:26:16,424 --> 01:26:19,577
Yeah, you sure did, and I got
the letter in here. Hold on.

1318
01:26:19,677 --> 01:26:21,204
Look what you said here.

1319
01:26:21,304 --> 01:26:25,166
"Dear Santa: For Christmas I want
my family to get a Harrison.

1320
01:26:25,266 --> 01:26:26,626
Love, Noel."

1321
01:26:26,726 --> 01:26:28,294
No, Dad. What it says is:

1322
01:26:28,394 --> 01:26:33,841
"Dear Santa: All I want for Christmas
is my family together as one.

1323
01:26:33,941 --> 01:26:36,043
Love, me."

1324
01:26:42,033 --> 01:26:43,851
I get it.

1325
01:26:43,951 --> 01:26:45,228
Me too.

1326
01:26:45,328 --> 01:26:48,815
"Together as one."

1327
01:26:48,915 --> 01:26:51,726
Boy, we're a couple of doofuses,
you know that?

1328
01:26:53,586 --> 01:26:56,898
And look, Santa gave me
exactly what I asked for.

1329
01:26:57,423 --> 01:27:01,327
My family together as one.

1330
01:27:01,427 --> 01:27:02,904
Sweetheart.

1331
01:27:03,971 --> 01:27:07,074
That's so beautiful.

1332
01:27:10,311 --> 01:27:12,177
Here we go.

1333
01:27:12,277 --> 01:27:14,091
- Who's hungry?
- I am.

1334
01:27:14,191 --> 01:27:16,167
Don't worry. I'll have
it carved up in no time.

1335
01:27:16,267 --> 01:27:18,553
No, look, it's my house.
Let me carve that turkey.

1336
01:27:18,653 --> 01:27:21,723
Larry, the turkey is traditionally
carved by the paterfamilias.

1337
01:27:21,823 --> 01:27:24,392
There's a 7-year-old over there.
Watch your language.

1338
01:27:24,492 --> 01:27:26,561
- I'll carve the turkey.
- I have an idea.

1339
01:27:26,661 --> 01:27:30,857
Why don't you both carve the turkey,
since you're both my dads?

1340
01:27:30,957 --> 01:27:33,392
Well, I'm here now, sweetheart.

1341
01:27:42,010 --> 01:27:45,071
Well, who likes it extra crispy?

1342
01:27:46,139 --> 01:27:49,208
Why don't we go out for dinner?

1343
01:27:49,308 --> 01:27:51,628
- That sounds like a good idea.
- Sounds good to me.

1344
01:27:51,728 --> 01:27:54,714
See? Now you two can finally
agree on something.

1345
01:27:54,814 --> 01:27:57,133
- Why don't we do sushi?
- We'll get Mexican.

1346
01:27:57,233 --> 01:27:58,384
- Italian.
- Persian.

1347
01:27:58,484 --> 01:27:59,636
- Chinese.
- Mediterranean?

1348
01:27:59,736 --> 01:28:01,095
- Sloppy joe.
- Korean. French?

1349
01:28:01,195 --> 01:28:02,430
- You guys.
- Barbecue ribs.

1350
01:28:02,530 --> 01:28:04,849
Vegan. How about fondue?

1351
01:28:04,949 --> 01:28:07,117
You don't know what fondue is?

1352
01:28:07,118 --> 01:28:08,260
Oh, Larry.

